## Suggest without keyword - `↵` search - `⌘↵` open first link ("Feeling Lucky") - `⌥↵` copy first link (requires [ddgr](https://github.com/jarun/ddgr)) - `⇧↵` inline search (requires [ddgr](https://github.com/jarun/ddgr))
**Recommendations** - Deactivate Google as Fallback Search, since this workflow gives you more fine-grained fallbacks. - Deactivate entering URLs, since this workflow does that already. - In the Advanced Alfred Settings, assign the "Action all visible Results" to a modifier. This allows you to trigger multiple searches at the same time, or when using the inline search, to open multiple pages at once. (Best assign it to the ctrl-key, since it does not have any conflicts with this workflow.)
## Global Search Hotkey Selection is… - file path → reveal it in Finder - directory path → open directory in Finder - url → open in default browser - email → send eMail to that address - some other text → search for selection & open first search result ("I'm feeling lucky")
## Add link to selection - turns selected text into a markdown link, with the URL of the first search result for that text as URL for the markdown link. - requires [ddgr](https://github.com/jarun/ddgr)
---
Created by [Chris Grieser](https://chris-grieser.de/).
